item.dc:creator: @cooper cooper
item.description:
@cooper wrote:

[quote=“thepinksock, post:12, topic:396538”]Yeah it was Susie that cheated. I’m on 20mg of Citalopram. It seems to be working great for me. They told me not to drink alcohol with it. Yet when I do I feel like all my anxiety is gone and I can talk to girls a lot easier.

Dappy introduced me to weed. Generally I don’t care if we never actually hook in to a relationship I’m just glad we’re friends, she’s an awesome person. (And also offered to beat the shit out of susie if we ever come across her )[/quote]
I’m sorry I’m glad that you’ve been able to move past it, though. Haha, yeah… antidepressants like citalopram often raise in effectiveness when drunk, however I can’t remember what side effects there are, it’s been a while since I took citalopram. I believe it’s similar to a ballmer peak, it’s great up to a point and then you’re in the shit.
